Name: SAW MISSION NUMBER
Explanation: PROVIDES THE IDENTIFIER FOR A SURFACE-TO-AIR MISSION.

Name: EQUIPMENT SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: ANY IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED BY CFE TREATY NATIONS WITHOUT STANDARDIZATION (E.G. 1N5-28) SEE AC/319-N/88.

Name: TASK NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ATP 6.

Name: INTERNET PROTOCOL (IP) ADDRESS OCTET
Explanation: THE INTERNET PROTOCOL (IP) ADDRESS OCTET.

Name: MINE LINE SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ATP 6.

Name: AEW SORTIE NUMBER SERIAL
Explanation: THIS CODE IS A COMPUTER GENERATED UNIQUE NUMBER CREATED BY AEW INTERNAL AUTOMATIC SYSTEM. ONLY USED WITH AEW UNIT CODE IN COMPOSITE FFIRN 2463 TO ENTER AEW SORTIE NUMBER.

Name: AEW REQUEST IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF THE REQUEST FOR THE AEW MISSION WHICH HAS TO BE PERFORMED. THE NUMBER WILL BE TWO DIGITS FOR THE CAOC OR REQUESTING AGENCY, 2 DIGITS FOR THE YEAR, AND FOUR DIGITS FOR THE REQUEST NUMBER.

Name: NAVAL AMPHIBIOUS COMMUNICATIONS NET LINE NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ACP 176.

Name: ACP 176 NATO SUPP 1C SHIP-SHORE TABLE NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ACP 176.

Name: SHIP-SHORE LINE NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ATP 2.

Name: CONVOY SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ATP 2.

Name: ACP 176 NATO SUPP 1C LOCAL HARBOUR COMMS TABLE NUMBER
EXERCISE PLATFORM EMITTING SIGNAL SERIAL NUMBER
HULL NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SPECIFIC VESSEL, WHICH WHEN ASSOCIATED WITH A SPECIFIC HULL TYPE OR SHIP TYPE, UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES THAT VESSEL. SEE STANAG 1005.

Name: TOWLINE NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF THE TOWLINE ASSIGNED DURING THE AIR TO AIR REFUELLING.

Name: UNIT NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMERICAL DESIGNATION ASSIGNED TO A MILITARY ORGANIZATION BY APPROPRIATE AUTHORITY.

Name: DOCUMENT SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: SEE ATP 6.

Name: ELINT NOTATION
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ELINT NOTATION FOR NON-COMMUNICATIONS ELECTRONIC EMISSIONS RELATED TO SUCH EQUIPMENTS. THE ELINT NOTATION IS EXTRACTED FROM THE LATEST EDITION OF THE ELINT PARAMETER LIST.

Name: NUMERICAL TARGET DESIGNATOR
Explanation: A FOUR DIGIT NUMERICAL GROUP WHICH DESIGNATES EACH SPECIFIC TARGET AS A SEPARATE ENTITY.

Name: MAGNETIC ANOMALY DETECTOR SENSOR SETTING
Explanation: THE NUMERICAL SENSE SETTING OF THE MAGNETIC ANOMALY DETECTION SENSITIVITY SETTING.

Name: WORLD AREA NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF THE WORLD AREA (FORMERLY THE WORLD AERONAUTICAL CHART NUMBER) IN WHICH A DESIGNATED PLACE, INSTALLATION, OR AREA IS LOCATED. SEE STANAG 2029.

Name: AIR CONTROL OPTION NUMBER
Explanation: THE AIR CONTROL OPTION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT

Name: FLIGHT LEVEL NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER USED TO IDENTIFY AN AIRCRAFT HEIGHT EXPRESSED AS A PRESSURE ALTITUDE IN HUNDREDS OF FEET.

Name: DEFECT NUMBER
Explanation: A DEFECT NUMBER MAY BE 2 LETTERS FOLLOWED BY 1-3 NUMERALS, A HYPHEN AND THE YEAR EXPRESSED AS 2 NUMERALS.

Name: PENNANT NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION OF A SPECIFIC VESSEL BY A COMBINATION OF LETTERS AND/OR NUMBERS BASED UPON COUNTRY OF REGISTRY.

Name: AIRCRAFT BUREAU NUMBER
Explanation: THE SERIAL NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT BY THE MANUFACTURER.

Name: MEDICAL ITEM GROUP NUMBER
Explanation: THE MEDICAL ITEM GROUP NUMBER OF THOSE ITEMS UNDER 10 DAYS OF SUPPLY.

Name: TARGET GROUP NUMBER
Explanation: THE GROUP NUMBER IN WHICH A TARGET IS ASSIGNED.

Name: TRACK IDENTIFIER
Explanation: PROVIDES THE TRACK IDENTIFIER EXPRESSED IN 4-NUMBER CODES.

Name: NATIONAL SHORT CODE
Explanation: SEE AOP-6(G).

Name: REFERENCE SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: A SERIAL NUMBER OR UNIQUE CHARACTER COMBINATION USED TO IDENTIFY A REFERENCE MESSAGE, DOCUMENT OR OTHER INFORMATION EXCHANGE.

Name: CONTACT SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: SEQUENTIAL NUMBERING OF MULTIPLE CONTACTS BY TYPE WITHIN A SINGLE MESSAGE.

Name: PRIORITY RANKING
Explanation: THE PRIORITY RANKING FOR AN INTELLIGENCE COLLECTION REQUEST RELATIVE TO OTHER REQUESTS FROM THE SAME USER.

Name: ORIGINATORS CONTROL REFERENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE CONTROL REFERENCE NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE ORIGINATOR OF A MESSAGE.

Name: STOCK NUMBER
Explanation: THE STOCK IDENTIFICATION NUMBER OF AN ARTICLE.

Name: MISSION NUMBER OF DELAYED FLIGHT
Explanation: THE MISSION NUMBER OF A FLIGHT THAT HAS BEEN DELAYED.

Name: NUMBER OF THE BUOY
Explanation: IDENTIFICATION NUMBER OF THE FORWARD AND AFT ESCAPE BUOY.

Name: SORTING CODE
Explanation: A 4-CHARACTER CODE WHICH FACILITATES REPORTING EQUIPMENT TYPE THAT HAS NO ASSOCIATED ELINT NOTATION.

Name: CODE DAY NUMBER
Explanation: PERIODS WHEN THE CODES ARE IN USE, FOR EXAMPLE: "DAY15".

Name: AIRCRAFT IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE TAIL, SIDE, OR WING NUMBER OF AN INDIVIDUAL AIRCRAFT.

Name: REPORT SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: USED TO SEQUENTIALLY NUMBER REPORTS TWO-CHARACTER PRODUCER CODE FOLLOWED BY 4 CHARACTER SEQUENCE NUMBER (AANNNN OR AAANNN).

Name: MAD OPERATIONAL EFFECTIVENESS AREA
Explanation: THE NUMERICAL DESIGNATION OF THE MAD OPERATIONAL EFFECTIVENESS AREA.

Name: RAW SCORE ACHIEVED
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM QUALIFICATION RAW SCORE ACHIEVED IN PERCENT.

Name: RAW SCORE AVAILABLE
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM QUALIFICATION RAW SCORE OR THE NUMBER OF POINTS AVAILABLE FOR THE EXERCISE.

Name: MINEFIELD DESIGNATOR
Explanation: THE NUMERICAL DESIGNATOR FROM THE OPERATIONAL TASKING AUTHORITY.

Name: REFERENCE POINT IDENTIFIER
Explanation: A SERIAL NUMBER WHICH IDENTIFIES AN AREA.

Name: AIRCRAFT SIDE NUMBER
Explanation: A COMBINATION OF NOSE AND TAIL NUMBERS THAT APPEAR ON THE NOSE AND TAIL OF AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: SORTIE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IDENTITY OF CONTROLLED AIR ASSET.

Name: AIRCRAFT TAIL LETTERS AND SIDE NUMBER
TANKER DATA LINK ADDRESS
Explanation: THE DATA LINK ADDRESS OF THE AIR-TO-AIR REFUELLING TANKER THAT REPRESENTS THE SOURCE/DESTINATION OF THE MESSAGE.

Name: UNIDENTIFIED ADDRESSING NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER USED TO IDENTIFY AN UNIDENTIFIED ENEMY UNIT.

Name: UNKNOWN ADDRESSING NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER USED TO IDENTIFY AN UNKNOWN ENEMY UNIT.

Name: GATEWAY REQUEST NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFYING NUMBER OF A GATEWAY REQUEST. IAW STANAG 4211.

Name: COMMUNICATIONS GATEWAY NATIONAL AREA CODE
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214, A 3-DIGIT AREA CODE.

Name: CONTROLLING SIDE SEP DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: CONTROLLING SIDE OSC DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: CONTROLLING SIDE FC DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: SUBORDINATE SIDE SEP DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: SUBORDINATE SIDE OSC DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: SUBORDINATE SIDE FC DIRECTORY NUMBER IDENTIFIER
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4214.

Name: NUMBER OF ENEMY MISSILES LAUNCHED
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF ENEMY SURFACE-TO-AIR MISSILES FIRED.

Name: SPOT NUMBER
Explanation: SPOT NUMBER IS A UNIQUE 5 DIGIT NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN EMITTER.

Name: AIRCRAFT DATA LINK ADDRESS
Explanation: THE DATA LINK ADDRESS OF THE AIRCRAFT THAT REPRESENTS THE SOURCE/DESTINATION OF THE MESSAGE.

Name: CARGO IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A PIECE OF CARGO.

Name: TRANSPORTATION CONTROL NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO CONTROL A SHIPMENT, OR A UNIT OF CARGO WITHIN A CONSOLIDATED SHIPMENT.

Name: BARGE NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION OR SERIAL NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A CARGO BARGE.

Name: VOYAGE NUMBER
Explanation: A DOCUMENT NUMBER ASSIGNED TO EACH VOYAGE.

Name: HATCH NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMERICAL DESIGNATION OF THE HATCH IN WHICH CARGO IS STOWED.

Name: REQUEST IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFYING NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SPECIFIC MISSION REQUEST BY THE REQUESTING ORGANIZATION.

Name: TASK IDENTIFIER
Explanation: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER TO RECORD THE REQUEST FOR FUTURE REFERENCE.

Name: NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP NUMBER
Explanation: LINK 16 NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP NUMBER.

Name: NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP OPTION NUMBER
Explanation: LINK 16 NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP OPTION NUMBER.

Name: SECURE DATA UNIT (SDU) LOCATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE SECURE DATA UNIT (SDU) LOCATION NUMBER FOR THE CRYPTOVARIABLE LOGICAL LABEL (CVLL).

Name: AIR CONTROL SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE AIR CONTROL OPTION SEQUENCE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: POINT IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTITY, NAME OR DESIGNATION OF A GEOGRAPHIC POINT OF REFERENCE.

Name: MAIN IJMS NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMERIC IDENTIFIER OF THE MAIN IJMS DATA LINK NET.

Name: ECM RESISTANT VOICE (ERV) NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMERIC IDENTIFIER OF AN ECM RESISTANT VOICE (ERV) NET.

Name: ECM RESISTANT VOICE (ERV) CHANNEL NUMBER
Explanation: AN ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER OF AN ECM RESISTANT VOICE (ERV) NET CHANNEL.

Name: MISSILE SHORT RANGE AIR DEFENCE ENGAGEMENT ZONE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: AN IDENTIFIER FOR THE MISSILE/SHORT RANGE AIR DEFENCE ENGAGEMENT ZONE

Name: VERTREP COMMUNICATIONS REQUIREMENTS
Explanation: THE VERTREP COMMUNICATIONS REQUIREMENTS BY LINE NUMBER, DEFINED WITH ALPHANUMERIC CHARACTERS.

Name: FAC DATA LINK ADDRESS
Explanation: THE DATA LINK ADDRESS OF THE FORWARD AIR CONTROLLER (FAC) THAT REPRESENTS THE SOURCE/DESTINATION OF THE MESSAGE.

Name: NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP (NPG) SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP (NPG) SEQUENCE NUMBER.

Name: RECEIVER DATA LINK ADDRESS
Explanation: EXPLANATION - THE DATA LINK ADDRESS OF THE RECEIVER AIRCRAFT THAT REPRESENTS THE SOURCE/DESTINATION OF THE MESSAGE.

Name: NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE ORIGINAL TRANSMISSION OR RELAY TRANSMIT NET NUMBER.

Name: MAGNETIC DEGAUSSING CODE NUMBER
Explanation: THE PEAK VERTICAL COMPONENT OF THE MAGNETIC FIELD IN MICROTESLA UNDER A SHIP ON THE WORST HEADING AND AT CERTAIN DEPTH.

Name: FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER NPG NUMBER
Explanation: THE FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER OPTION NUMBER
Explanation: THE FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER OPTION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: NUMBER OF TONE KEY
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF THE TONE KEY ASSIGNED.

Name: FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER SEQUENCE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: TACAN CHANNEL NUMBER
Explanation: THE SPECIFIC NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE NUMERIC PORTION OF A TACAN CHANNEL.

Name: NUMBER OF ENEMY GUNS FIRED
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF ENEMY ANTI-AIRCRAFT ARTILLERY GUNS FIRED.

Name: CRYPTO PUBLICATION LINE NUMBER
Explanation: THE CRYPTO PUBLICATION LINE NUMBER (0001-9999) OF A UNIT.

Name: CARGO CLASSIFICATION
Explanation: THE SECURITY CLASSIFICATION OF SPECIAL CARGO WHICH THEREFORE REQUIRES SPECIAL HANDLING OR PREPARATION.

Name: NETWORK PARTICIPANT RANGE
Explanation: THE NETWORK PARTICIPANT NUMBER RANGE FOR A SQUADRON OF AIRCRAFT.

Name: WAVE OR PRE ASSAULT WAVE NUMBER
Explanation: THE SEQUENCE NUMBER REPRESENTING A WAVE OR PRE-ASSAULT WAVE (PREFIX P) IN AN AMPHIBIOUS LANDING.

Name: AIR SORTIE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER (1-999) OF AIR SORTIE.

Name: CRAFT NUMBER
Explanation: A SEQUENTIAL IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO A LANDING CRAFT OR AIRCRAFT IN AN AMPHIBIOUS ASSAULT WAVE.

Name: FIRE SUPPORT REFERENCE POINT NUMBER
Explanation: A SEQUENTIAL DESIGNATOR ASSIGNED TO A FIRE SUPPORT REFERENCE POINT.

Name: FIRE SUPPORT STATION DESIGNATOR
Explanation: A SEQUENTIAL DESIGNATOR, CONTAINING ARABIC NUMERALS, ASSIGNED TO A FIRE SUPPORT STATION.

Name: FIRE SUPPORT AREA DESIGNATOR
Explanation: A SEQUENTIAL DESIGNATOR, CONTAINING ROMAN NUMERALS, ASSIGNED TO A FIRE SUPPORT AREA.

Name: ZONE OF FIRE DESIGNATOR
Explanation: A SEQUENTIAL DESIGNATOR ASSIGNED TO A ZONE OF FIRE IN FIRE SUPPORT OPERATIONS.

Name: SERIAL ASSIGNMENT NUMBER
Explanation: A 4-DIGIT NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A CARGO SERIAL.

Name: SPOT ALLOCATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE OCTAL CODE REFERRING TO CATEGORIES WITHIN A SPOT NUMBER.

Name: PERSONAL IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A PERSON FOR UNIQUE IDENTIFICATION.

Name: PW INTERROGATION SERIAL NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER ALLOCATED BY THE INTERROGATION UNIT FIRST DEALING WITH THE PW TO IDENTIFY THE SOURCE OF INFORMATION. THE CONSTITUTION OF A PW INTERROGATION SERIAL NUMBER IS DETAILED IN ANNEX B TO STANAG 2033.

Name: SET SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER INDICATING THE SEQUENTIAL POSITION OF THE SET FORMAT COUNTED FROM THE FIRST SET (EXER OR OPER, OR MSGID IF EXER OR OPER ARE NOT USED) OF THE REFERENCED MESSAGE.

Name: DATA LINE SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER INDICATING THE POSITION OF THE TARGETED LINE WITHIN THE PARTICULAR COLUMNAR SET FORMAT BEING AMENDED. THE HEADER LINE IS ALWAYS DATA LINE SEQUENCE NUMBER 1, WITH FOLLOWING DATA LINES NUMBERED SEQUENTIALLY BEGINNING WITH 2.

Name: IMAGE NUMBER
Explanation: INDICATES AN IMAGERY FRAME NUMBER, SEQUENCE OF FRAME NUMBERS, OR AN INCLUSIVE SET OF FRAME NUMBERS.

Name: UN NA IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: SEE STANAG 2909

Name: AIRLIFT MISSION NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER ASSIGNED TO MISSIONS TO MANAGE THEIR ACTIVITIES.

Name: RENDEZVOUS AIRCRAFT MISSION NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO IDENTIFY ONE AIRCRAFT FROM ANOTHER.

Name: AIMPOINT SUFFIX
Explanation: A TWO-CHARACTER SUFFIX FOR A BE NUMBER.

Name: SPECIAL HULL NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SPECIFIC VESSEL, WHICH WHEN ASSOCIATED WITH A SPECIFIC HULL TYPE OR CLASS OF VESSEL, UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES THAT VESSEL.

Name: UNIT LINE NUMBER
Explanation: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER FOR A TIME PHASE FORCE DEPLOYMENT DATA ELEMENT AND CAN BE BROKEN INTO MORE SPECIFIC ELEMENTS SUCH AS UIC.

Name: LEG IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFYING NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SINGLE LEG OF A MISSION.

Name: REQUIREMENT NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO UNIQUELY IDENTIFY EACH REQUIREMENT.

Name: ONLOAD LEG REFERENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO IDENTIFY THE CARGO ONLOAD LEG OF AN AIRLIFT MISSION.

Name: OFFLOAD LEG REFERENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO IDENTIFY THE CARGO OFFLOAD LEG OF AN AIRLIFT MISSION.

Name: PERSONNEL INCREMENT NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER THAT UNIQUELY DEFINES EACH NON-UNIT PERSONNEL RECORD.

Name: CARGO INCREMENT NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER THAT UNIQUELY DEFINES EACH NON-UNIT CARGO RECORD.

Name: CELL SEQUENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE TANKERS POSITION WITHIN THE AIR REFUELLING CELL.

Name: LASER CORRELATION CODE
Explanation: A CODE THAT ENSURES CORRELATION BETWEEN TARGET DESIGNATION SYSTEM AND WEAPON DELIVERY SYSTEM.

Name: RECEIVER TACAN CHANNEL
Explanation: PROVIDES THE NUMBER OF THE TACAN CHANNEL OF THE RECEIVER AIRCRAFT DURING REFUELLING, AS DESCRIBED BY THE RELEVANT STANAG 5034.

Name: TANKER TACAN CHANNEL
Explanation: PROVIDES THE NUMBER OF THE TACAN CHANNEL OF THE TANKER DURING REFUELLING, AS DESCRIBED BY THE RELEVANT STANAG 5034.

Name: POINT NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A ROUTE POINT OR OTHER REFERENCE POINT.

Name: PRIMARY CONFIGURATION LOAD
Explanation: THE CONFIGURATION OF THE PRIMARY LOAD OF AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: SECONDARY CONFIGURATION LOAD
Explanation: THE CONFIGURATION OF THE SECONDARY LOAD OF AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: COORDINATE SEQUENCE
Explanation: A NUMBER WHICH INDICATES THE SEQUENCE ORDER OF A SPECIFIC COORDINATE BOUNDING AN AREA, INSTALLATION OR FACILITY.

Name: PLACE ACCESSION NUMBER
Explanation: UNIQUE ONE-UP (ROLL-UP) NUMBER GENERATED BY THE RESPONSIBLE PRODUCER (RESPROD) FIRST IDENTIFYING THE PLACE. [REF: STANAG 2439, AINTP-3]

Name: STREET NUMBER
Explanation: HOUSE NUMBER, POST OFFICE BOX, POSTAL STOP, APARTMENT NUMBER, RURAL ROUTE NUMBER, BUILDING NUMBER, ROOM NUMBER, OFFICE OR EQUIVALENT NUMBER USED IN AN ADDRESS. [REF: AINTP-3]

Name: PRIMARY CONFIGURATION CODE
Explanation: THE PRIMARY ORDNANCE MIX CARRIED ON A MISSION AIRCRAFT.

Name: SECONDARY CONFIGURATION CODE
Explanation: THE SECONDARY ORDNANCE MIX CARRIED ON A MISSION AIRCRAFT.

Name: EQUIPMENT ACCESSION NUMBER
Explanation: CONSISTS OF AN ALPHA CHARACTER DEFINING THE TYPE OF EQUIPMENT WITH A UNIQUE SEQUENTIAL NUMBER GENERATED BY THE RESPONSIBLE PRODUCER WHO FIRST IDENTIFIED THE EQUIPMENT. [REF: STANAG 2097, AINTP-3]

Name: FIELD POST NUMBER
Explanation: THE MILITARY POSTAL CODE USED BY A UNIT. [REF: STANAG 2438, AINTP-3]

Name: UNIT ACCESSION NUMBER
Explanation: CONSISTS OF A UNIQUE SEQUENTIAL NUMBER GENERATED BY THE RESPONSIBLE PRODUCER (RESPROD) WHO FIRST IDENTIFIED THE UNIT. [REF: STANAG 2438, AINTP-3]

Name: EVENT ACCESSION NUMBER
Explanation: UNIQUE SEQUENTIAL NUMBER GENERATED BY THE RESPONSIBLE PRODUCER (RESPROD) WHO FIRST IDENTIFIES THE EVENT. [REF: STANAG 2441, AINTP-3]

Name: TRACK LEG
Explanation: THE SEQUENTIAL NUMBER OF A POINT IN AN AIRSPACE TRACK.

Name: GRID CENTRE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER GIVEN TO THE CENTRE POINT OF A GRID USED FOR THE DISPOSITION OF MARITIME FORCES.

Name: COMPOSITE AIR OPERATIONS (COMAO) IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO A COMPOSITE AIR OPERATIONS (COMAO) FORCE.

Name: MISSION NUMBER SUPPORTED
Explanation: THE MISSION NUMBER OF THE MISSION BEING ESCORTED.

Name: NET IN USE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER OF THE HAVE QUICK NET IN USE.

Name: SET IN USE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER OF THE HAVE QUICK SET IN USE.

Name: LINK NUMBER
Explanation: ARBITRARY NUMBER ALLOCATED BY THE RECORD ORIGINATOR TO THE LINK.

Name: IDENTIFICATION CODE NUMBER
Explanation: THE CODE NUMBER THAT IDENTIFIES THE PARTICULAR CONVEYANCE TO BE USEDTO TRANSPORT PERSONNEL AND/OR CARGO.

Name: IDENTIFIER OF THE SONOBUOY IN PATTERN GAINING CONTACT
RENDEZVOUS BREAKUP TACAN CHANNEL
Explanation: THE TACAN CHANNEL NUMBER USED BY THE RENDEZVOUS/BREAKUP PARTICIPANTS.

Name: MEDIA REFERENCE NUMBER
Explanation: THE ASSIGNED REFERENCE NUMBER THAT CORRESPONDS WITH MEDIA TYPE AND ADDRESS REPORTED.

Name: MOBILE TARGET NUMBER
Explanation: THE UNIQUE IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO A MOBILE TARGET.

Name: ROE NUMBER
Explanation: AN ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER THAT SPECIFIES THE NUMBER, AND IF APPLICABLE, THE PARAGRAPH OF THE ROE BEING INVOKED.

Name: POSITION IDENTIFYING NUMBER
Explanation: IDENTIFIES THE POSITION INSIDE THE SEQUENCE OF COLUMNS OIN WHICH A COLUMN IS TO MOVE ON A ROAD MOVEMENT.

Name: SURFACE TRANSPORT REPLY NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER THAT IDENTIFIES THE REPLY TO A SURFACE TRANSPORT REQUEST.

Name: NATIONAL IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SPECIFIC TRAIN DEPARTING A NATION ON A PARTICULAR DAY.

Name: UNIFIED (RAIL) SKETCH BOOK NUMBER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER OF THE SHEET WITHIN THE UNIFIED SKETCH BOOK FOR EXCEPTIONAL MILITARY EQUIPMENT THAT DESCRIBES THE SPECIFIC EQUIPMENT TO BE TRANSPORTED. SEE STANAG 2175.

Name: IMAGERY ACCESSION NUMBER
Explanation: A UNIQUE SEQUENTIAL NUMBER ALLOCATED TO NEW IMAGERY RECORDS BY THE PRODUCING AGENCY. THIS ROLL-UP NUMBER IS USUALLY SYSTEM MACHINE GENERATED, BUT CAN BE MANUALLY INSERTED.

Name: TARGET LIST NUMBER
Explanation: A NUMERIC IDENTIFIER OF A TARGET LIST.

Name: POST OFFICE BOX NUMBER
Explanation: INDICATES THE POST OFFICE BOX NUMBER USED BY THE ENTITY.

Name: TERMINAL AREA MODEL IDENTIFICATION
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION FOR THE TERMINAL AREA MODEL FOR THE JOINT AIR TO SURFACE STANDOFF MISSILE.

Name: 4W GRID ROW
Explanation: IDENTIFIES A ROW IN A 4W GRID, ATP 1 VOL 1 CHAP 3

Name: 4W GRID COLUMN
Explanation: IDENTIFIES A COLUMN IN A 4W GRID, ATP 1 VOL 1 CHAP 3

Name: OFFICIAL CASUALTY NUMBER
Explanation: THIS IS A NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE MEDICAL REPORTING TEAM TO A PARTICULAR CASUALTY. THIS NUMBER STAYS WITH THE CASUALTY UNTIL HE/SHE IS POSITIVELY IDENTIFIED AND/OR CAN REPORT HIS NATIONAL NUMBER.

Name: MOVEMENT IDENTIFICATION NUMBER
Explanation: PROVIDES THE UNIQUE IDENTIFIER ALLOCATED BY THE MOVEMENT CONTROL AGENCY AS IN AMOVP1 CHAPTER 5.

Name: SOR NUMBER
Explanation: ONE THROUGH EIGHT DIGIT NUMBER IDENTIFYING A CERTAIN STATEMENT OF REQUIREMENT.

Name: SERVICE NUMBER
Explanation: AN ALPHANUMERIC IDENTIFIER ALLOCATED BY A NATION TO EACH INDIVIDUAL SERVING IN THEIR ARMED FORCES.

Name: NATIONAL STOCK NUMBER
Explanation: THE STOCK IDENTIFICATION NUMBER OF AN ARTICLE.

Name: NUMBER OF THE SPAN BEING REPORTED ON
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF THE SPAN WITHIN THE BRIDGE BEING REPORTED.

Name: MCCIS TRACK NUMBER
Explanation: A 5-CHARACTER ALPHANUMERIC REFERENCE GIVEN TO A CONTACT REPORTED IN THE MARITIME COMMAND, CONTROL AND INFORMATION SYSTEM (MCCIS).

Name: SEQUENTIAL NUMBER
Explanation: SEQUENTIAL NUMBER 1 THROUGH 999.

Name: ALPHABETIC SUFFIX (A-Z)
Explanation: A ONE LETTER ALPHABETIC SUFFIX, A THROUGH Z.

Name: SOFTWARE RELEASE
Explanation: A UNIQUE DESIGNATOR OF A SOFTWARE RELEASE.

Name: SADL AIR KEY
Explanation: THE KEY FOR ESTABLISHING THE SADL NET PLAYERS THAT WILL BE DISPLAYED.

Name: GUARD CHANNEL NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER REPRESENTING THE SETTING FOR THE GUARD CHANNEL TO BE USED.

Name: RF CHANNEL HOP SET NUMBER
Explanation: THE NUMBER REPRESENTING THE SETTING FOR THE RF CHANNEL HOP TO BE USED.

Name: SADL FREQUENCY MAP
Explanation: THE FREQUENCY ON WHICH THE RADIO WILL OPERATE IN A SITUATION AWARENESS DATALINK (SADL).

Name: SADL GATEWAY KEY
Explanation: THE KEY TO SELECT THE SPECIFIC GATEWAY TO BE USED.

Name: TCP IP PORT NUMBER
Explanation: THE PORT USED FOR THE TCP/IP CONNECTION.

Name: BRIGADE LOGICAL CHANNEL NUMBER
Explanation: THE BRIGADE LOGICAL CHANNEL NUMBER TO RECEIVE BRIGADE SITUATIONAL AWARENESS DATA LINK INFORMATION.

Name: BATTALION LOGICAL CHANNEL NUMBER
Explanation: THE BATTALION LOGICAL CHANNEL NUMBER TO RECEIVE BRIGADE SITUATIONAL AWARENESS DATA LINK INFORMATION.

Name: SOURCE LINK DESIGNATOR
Explanation: THE SOURCE LINK DESIGNATOR DESIGNATED FOR FORWARDING.

Name: EPLRS DIVISION
Explanation: THE DIVISION IDENTIFICATION USED TO INDICATE AN EPLRS SETTING.

Name: GROUND KEY FREQUENCY MAP
Explanation: THE FREQUENCY ON WHICH THE RADIO WILL OPERATE IN A SITUATION AWARENESS DATA LINK (SADL) ENVIRONMENT.

Name: GUARD NUMBER
Explanation: THE GUARD NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A SATELLITE.

Name: AIR CONTROL NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE JTIDS/MIDS NET NUMBER ASSIGNED TO AN AIRCRAFT FOR AIR CONTROL.

Name: FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP (NPG) NET NUMBER BEING USED FOR FIGHTER-TO-FIGHTER DATA LINK COMMUNICATIONS

Name: ANCHORAGE IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFIER OF AN ANCHORAGE.

Name: AEW NET CODE
Explanation: THE FOUR LETTER CODE IDENTIFYING AN AEW NET.

Name: AEW NET NUMBER
Explanation: THE FOUR DIGIT INCREMENTAL CODE IDENTIFYING AN AEW NET.

Name: AEW NET QUALIFIER
Explanation: THE ONE LETTER CODE QUALIFYING THE TYPE OF AEW NET.
